One natural talent I've always been keen on improving is playing the guitar. I discovered my interest in this instrument during my early teenage years. An acquaintance of my family who was quite the musician himself, gave me my first guitar. He taught me a few chords, and since then, I was hooked. I was fascinated by the promise of creating beautiful melodies that really resonated with me.
To improve my guitar playing, I've been thinking about taking more structured lessons. Up until now, I've been mostly self-taught, navigating through online tutorials and experimenting on my own. However, I believe hierarchical lessons could really help refine my technique and expand my knowledge of music theory. I aim to enhance my technical proficiency by practicing scales and challenging myself with more complex fingergings. I also plan to practice more consistently - aiming for at least one hour a day.
Honestly, playing the guitar is incredibly fulfilling for me. Every time, I pick up the instrument, whether to strum a simple chord progression or attempt a new fingerstyle technique, I feel a rush a joy and satisfaction. It' also a way of expressing my emotions and retreating into myself after a long day at work. That's why I'm so eager to get better at it.
Ultimately, improving my guitar skills would not only allow me to enjoy playing more but also share more beautiful music with others. I can't wait to see where this journey takes me.

